hymns.text:
p: Now praise, as one who strives for strength, the harnessing of Agni's car, the liberal, the most splendid One;

p: Who, guiding worshippers aright, withers, untouched by age, the foe: When worshipped fair to look upon;

p: Who for his glory is extolled at eve and morning in our homes, whose statute is inviolate;

p: Who shines refulgent like the Sun, with brilliance and with fiery flame, Decked with imperishable sheen.

p: Him Atri, Agni, have our songs Strengthened according to his sway: All glories hath he made his own.

p: May we with Agni's, indra's help, with Soma's, yea, of all the Devas, Uninjured dwell together still, and conquer those who fight with us.
